{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5076: A way to allow duplicate attribute in @vue/compiler-dom",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:56.903327+00:00",
  "text": "A way to allow duplicate attribute in @vue/compiler-dom\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\nsolves a parse failure in https://github.com/vitejs/vite/issues/5966\r\naccording to mentioned issue, duplicate class attributes are allowed in html\r\n\r\nrelated issue: https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next/issues/4883\r\n\r\n[Reproduction](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\na new option to to allow duplicate attributes\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have"
  ],
